Ohanaeze Ndigbo Worldwide has blamed Anambra Governor Chukwuma Soludo for the recent surge of killings in the State. Ohanaeze alleged Soludo is not defending the oath of office he took as the Chief Security Officer to protect the lives and properties of citizens in Anambra State. A statement by the Secretary General of Ohanaeze worldwide, Mazi Okechukwu Isiguzoro reads: “If there’s anybody to be blamed for the senseless killings in the state, Governor Chukwuma Soludo should be held accountable for the actions of these criminals. “This is not time to shift blames because the bucks stops at the Governor’s table, he should arrest the insecurity challenges confronting the people of Anambra State”.   Onor wins PDP Gov ticket in Cross River     Alleged drug deal: Kyari’s fresh bail motion stalls…     Abiodun wins Ogun APC Gov ticket   It added: ‘We condemned in strong terms the barbaric acts of violence and killing of the Adamawa pregnant woman and her kids. “We are aware of the fact that criminal elements have hijacked the violent agitation and turned it into a killing spree,” “North should accept our condolences, especially ACF and Arewa youths, we recommend the castration of those criminals ravaging the southeast. “Ohanaeze is ready to partner with the Government and people of Anambra to end this madness, this is the best time for action and not to make bogus speeches and take pictures in DSS facilities.”